                  </hi>. I had some wheat, which ought to have been in my bars—this sack of wheat was found in the bin, in the stable—it is mine—the prisoner had no business to take it—I said to him, "<hi rend="italic">Will</hi>, you have been robbing me"—he pleaded for mercy—he said before the Magistrate that he took it for his horses—I do not give wheat to horses; it would kill a horse, being new wheat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did you never know that wheat was very fattening to a horse? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; we always give wheat-chaff with the horses' food, but not wheat.</p>
